WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:21.780 --> 00:00:23.600
No. don't go!

2
00:00:24.650 --> 00:00:27.010
I'll be back. Little Flower.

3
00:00:27.210 --> 00:00:31.050
But until then.
you need to know something.

4
00:00:32.840 --> 00:00:35.200
Listen to that. Keyleth.

5
00:00:37.320 --> 00:00:40.190
- Do you hear it?
- The wind?

6
00:00:40.390 --> 00:00:42.460
Your power.

7
00:00:45.330 --> 00:00:46.780
Whoa.

8
00:00:46.980 --> 00:00:48.920
Now. listen to that.

9
00:00:50.130 --> 00:00:52.820
Wind. fire.

10
00:00:53.020 --> 00:00:55.180
And the earth and water.

11
00:01:01.140 --> 00:01:03.130
- Ow.
- Ah.

12
00:01:03.330 --> 00:01:06.480
Never pull back. Here.

13
00:01:08.060 --> 00:01:10.380
See?

14
00:01:10.580 --> 00:01:12.550
Flame cannot live without air.

15
00:01:12.750 --> 00:01:16.060
and we are Air Ashari.
are we not?

16
00:01:16.260 --> 00:01:19.350
We were made
to pass through fire.

17
00:01:19.550 --> 00:01:21.390
It doesn't hurt you?

18
00:01:21.590 --> 00:01:23.690
Only if you let it.

19
00:01:26.930 --> 00:01:29.940
- Time for Mom to go.
- Can I go with you?

20
00:01:30.140 --> 00:01:32.160
You'll always be with me.

21
00:01:32.350 --> 00:01:35.280
And one day. you'll be ready
for your own journey.

22
00:01:35.480 --> 00:01:37.180
You only have to listen.

23
00:03:11.150 --> 00:03:14.130
And then. whoosh.
I was alive again.

24
00:03:14.330 --> 00:03:16.880
It really puts life
into perspective. you know?

25
00:03:17.080 --> 00:03:19.300
I feel more grown. more mature.

26
00:03:19.500 --> 00:03:21.470
Eh. you look more mature.

27
00:03:21.670 --> 00:03:23.640
I'm going to take that
as a compliment

28
00:03:23.840 --> 00:03:25.770
because of how mature I am.

29
00:03:25.970 --> 00:03:27.190
Vax gets it.

30
00:03:27.390 --> 00:03:28.940
- Right. brother?
- Sure.

31
00:03:29.140 --> 00:03:32.320
Whole new perspective.

32
00:03:32.520 --> 00:03:34.150
Uh. Keyleth?

33
00:03:34.350 --> 00:03:36.610
Keyleth.

34
00:03:36.810 --> 00:03:40.450
- Is something wrong?
- No. nothing.

35
00:03:40.650 --> 00:03:44.160
It's just.
we're so close to Pyrah.

36
00:03:44.360 --> 00:03:45.830
Is that where you're from?

37
00:03:46.030 --> 00:03:47.620
No. I'm an Air Ashari.

38
00:03:47.820 --> 00:03:49.830
The Fire Ashari live there.

39
00:03:50.030 --> 00:03:51.710
guarding the rift
to the Fire Plane.

40
00:03:51.910 --> 00:03:53.500
It was one of the last places

41
00:03:53.700 --> 00:03:57.300
my mom was seen alive
on her Aramenté.

42
00:03:57.500 --> 00:04:00.300
Oh. Keyleth. I'm so sorry.

43
00:04:00.500 --> 00:04:03.560
If we're close to Pyrah.
maybe we should go.

44
00:04:03.760 --> 00:04:07.440
I'd like to. but the people of
Tal'Dorei are depending on us.

45
00:04:07.630 --> 00:04:09.350
No. y-you're right.

46
00:04:09.550 --> 00:04:11.520
It's fine. I didn't mean to...

47
00:04:11.720 --> 00:04:13.960
I-I'm gonna go get more wood.

48
00:04:16.840 --> 00:04:19.410
Uh. how long has Grog been gone?

49
00:04:19.600 --> 00:04:21.530
Doesn't take that long
to pop a squat.

50
00:04:21.730 --> 00:04:24.120
This is Grog
we're talking about.

51
00:04:24.320 --> 00:04:26.950
I'll go check on him. Here.

52
00:04:27.150 --> 00:04:28.930
For the fire.

53
00:04:37.400 --> 00:04:40.300
Um. uh...

54
00:04:40.500 --> 00:04:41.640
Craven Edge?

55
00:04:41.840 --> 00:04:44.640
Yes?

56
00:04:44.840 --> 00:04:46.680
Ah. good. you're there.

57
00:04:46.880 --> 00:04:49.310
I hunger.

58
00:04:49.510 --> 00:04:51.230
Yep. for blood.

59
00:04:51.430 --> 00:04:54.480
Uh. look. so I love opening
people up to feed you. right?

60
00:04:54.680 --> 00:04:57.190
I mean. they're flying apart.
It's like a dream.

61
00:04:57.390 --> 00:04:58.900
Uh. but can I ask.

62
00:04:59.100 --> 00:05:02.410
could you ever be... full?

63
00:05:02.610 --> 00:05:04.240
Uh. Grog?

64
00:05:04.440 --> 00:05:06.240
- Are you talking to your dookie?
- Uh. yeah.

65
00:05:06.440 --> 00:05:07.870
Just asserting my dominance.

66
00:05:08.070 --> 00:05:10.330
Uh. can you play me a tune?

67
00:05:10.530 --> 00:05:12.170
You know. I just. uh.
I don't want anyone

68
00:05:12.370 --> 00:05:13.580
hearing me go boom-boom.

69
00:05:13.780 --> 00:05:16.960
Sure. yeah. Poop accompaniment.

70
00:05:17.160 --> 00:05:19.300
It's what I've been
training for my whole life.

71
00:05:19.500 --> 00:05:21.380
♪ <i>In an outhouse</i> ♪

72
00:05:21.580 --> 00:05:22.890
♪ <i>On the edge of the world...</i>

73
00:05:23.090 --> 00:05:25.100
Oh. so. um...

74
00:05:25.300 --> 00:05:27.970
- Uh. where was I?
- Uh. is this loud enough for you?

75
00:05:28.170 --> 00:05:29.680
Uh. yeah. yeah. that's good!

76
00:05:29.880 --> 00:05:33.060
Um. so I kind of
want to know. like. um.

77
00:05:33.260 --> 00:05:35.730
what's in this for you?

78
00:05:35.930 --> 00:05:38.780
The blood
of your enemies feeds me.

79
00:05:38.980 --> 00:05:41.530
Their strength becomes yours.

80
00:05:41.730 --> 00:05:43.700
That is our exchange.

81
00:05:43.900 --> 00:05:47.410
Is it? I mean. I am crazy.
no doubt. when I'm using you.

82
00:05:47.610 --> 00:05:50.870
- but it kind of feels...
- It matters not.

83
00:05:51.070 --> 00:05:54.000
All that matters is...

84
00:05:54.200 --> 00:05:55.880
Ooh. Sorry.

85
00:05:56.080 --> 00:05:59.810
I hunger. always.

86
00:06:01.360 --> 00:06:04.780
Man. I sympathize with that.

87
00:06:46.740 --> 00:06:48.260
No!

88
00:06:48.460 --> 00:06:50.100
Leave me alone!

89
00:06:53.300 --> 00:06:55.100
Vax. are-are you okay?

90
00:06:55.300 --> 00:06:58.560
Sorry. I must have dozed off.

91
00:06:58.760 --> 00:07:01.980
- Thought I saw dragons.
- Want me to take over?

92
00:07:02.180 --> 00:07:04.280
No. Rest.

93
00:07:04.480 --> 00:07:06.170
I just need to stretch my legs.

94
00:07:14.560 --> 00:07:15.620
Come on. damn it.

95
00:07:15.820 --> 00:07:18.390
Why won't you come off?

96
00:07:33.450 --> 00:07:35.020
Sing with me. buddy.

97
00:07:35.220 --> 00:07:37.140
♪ <i>Road. road.</i>
<i>we're on the road</i> ♪

98
00:07:37.340 --> 00:07:39.270
♪ <i>Road. road. we're on</i>
<i>the road</i> ♪

99
00:07:39.470 --> 00:07:43.230
♪ <i>Good thing you and me</i>
<i>ain't choads</i> ♪

100
00:07:43.430 --> 00:07:45.530
♪ <i>We're on the fucking road</i> ♪

101
00:07:45.730 --> 00:07:46.950
- Ha!
- Aah! Grog!

102
00:07:47.150 --> 00:07:48.450
Oh. sorry.

103
00:07:48.650 --> 00:07:50.570
You be careful. you big old boy.

104
00:07:50.770 --> 00:07:52.370
Feel better?

105
00:07:52.570 --> 00:07:55.330
I will when we get there.

106
00:08:02.690 --> 00:08:04.460
- Hey. Scanlan.
- Huh?

107
00:08:04.660 --> 00:08:06.630
You know all these
magical words and such.

108
00:08:06.830 --> 00:08:08.800
Mind taking a peek at this?

109
00:08:09.000 --> 00:08:10.590
What. you kept that thing?

110
00:08:10.790 --> 00:08:12.180
Huh. uh...

111
00:08:12.380 --> 00:08:14.270
"Volantire."

112
00:08:14.460 --> 00:08:17.100
- Oh.
- Holy shit.

113
00:08:17.300 --> 00:08:18.526
What did you...
How did you do that?

114
00:08:18.550 --> 00:08:22.150
What'd you say? Vertuna?
Viridian? Voluptuous?

115
00:08:22.350 --> 00:08:23.650
Mm. venereal.

116
00:08:23.850 --> 00:08:25.320
- Dick.
- Whoa.

117
00:08:25.520 --> 00:08:27.320
Okay. okay. okay.
how about this?

118
00:08:27.520 --> 00:08:29.950
I'll tell you the magic word
for a favor.

119
00:08:30.150 --> 00:08:31.280
What favor?

120
00:08:31.480 --> 00:08:32.950
Ooh. yeah. that's the thing.

121
00:08:33.150 --> 00:08:35.370
I'm not gonna tell you.
You just got to trust me.

122
00:08:35.570 --> 00:08:38.830
Ha. I've met cockroaches
more trustworthy than you.

123
00:08:39.030 --> 00:08:40.790
Volantire.

124
00:08:40.990 --> 00:08:42.710
- Whoa!
- Scanlan. you're a birdie.

125
00:08:44.950 --> 00:08:46.630
Vex. you are missing out.

126
00:08:46.830 --> 00:08:49.050
You really have
to experience it firsthand

127
00:08:49.250 --> 00:08:52.180
to truly... whoa...
Understand the-the...

128
00:08:52.380 --> 00:08:53.820
What?

129
00:08:55.820 --> 00:08:57.310
- Whoa.
- Scanlan!

130
00:08:57.510 --> 00:08:59.640
I swear to the gods.
I will restring your lute

131
00:08:59.840 --> 00:09:01.350
with your own pubic hairs!

132
00:09:01.550 --> 00:09:03.610
We don't have time for this.

133
00:09:03.810 --> 00:09:05.020
Uh. guys. there's a volcano.

134
00:09:05.220 --> 00:09:06.980
and it is more pissed off
than Vex.

135
00:09:07.180 --> 00:09:08.320
What?

136
00:09:08.520 --> 00:09:10.400
The volcano is supposed
to be dormant.

137
00:09:10.600 --> 00:09:12.990
Yeah? Well. it's not.

138
00:09:13.190 --> 00:09:15.740
No. The rift
to the Fire Plane is there.

139
00:09:15.940 --> 00:09:18.750
If it's erupting. then Pyrah...

140
00:09:18.950 --> 00:09:21.000
The Fire Ashari
could be in trouble.

141
00:09:21.200 --> 00:09:23.880
Then they'll have to deal
with it themselves.

142
00:09:24.080 --> 00:09:27.840
I'm sorry. Keyleth. but Osysa's
instructions were very clear.

143
00:09:28.040 --> 00:09:29.940
Well. uh... Vex.

144
00:09:36.280 --> 00:09:38.770
Keyleth!

145
00:09:38.970 --> 00:09:42.480
Man. you could go after her
if you had a flying broom.

146
00:09:42.680 --> 00:09:44.520
All of Tal'Dorei is in danger.

147
00:09:44.720 --> 00:09:47.820
We can't detour every time
we see someone in trouble.

148
00:09:48.020 --> 00:09:50.280
This isn't just someone
in trouble.

149
00:09:50.480 --> 00:09:51.700
It's her people.

150
00:09:51.900 --> 00:09:55.490
Brother. Keyleth would drop
everything to help us.

151
00:09:55.690 --> 00:09:57.620
Especially you.

152
00:10:15.290 --> 00:10:17.320
Help!

153
00:10:28.250 --> 00:10:29.480
It's okay.

154
00:10:29.680 --> 00:10:30.940
Get to your family.

155
00:10:31.140 --> 00:10:33.030
Thank you.

156
00:10:33.230 --> 00:10:34.990
Mother!

157
00:10:35.190 --> 00:10:37.300
Pyrah.

158
00:10:41.570 --> 00:10:42.830
Are you okay?

159
00:10:43.030 --> 00:10:45.330
More are coming through.

160
00:10:45.530 --> 00:10:47.130
- We need help.
- Dad?

161
00:10:47.330 --> 00:10:49.460
Keyleth.

162
00:10:52.080 --> 00:10:53.520
I didn't know
when I'd see you again.

163
00:10:53.670 --> 00:10:55.220
I can't believe you're here.

164
00:10:55.420 --> 00:10:57.820
You must have come
for your Aramenté.

165
00:10:58.860 --> 00:11:00.510
I-I. uh...

166
00:11:00.710 --> 00:11:03.480
Uh. what did this to Pyrah?
There are so many dead.

167
00:11:03.680 --> 00:11:06.100
The rift to the Fire Plane
was torn open.

168
00:11:06.300 --> 00:11:07.860
That's impossible.

169
00:11:08.050 --> 00:11:09.570
It's been secure
for generations.

170
00:11:09.760 --> 00:11:10.860
It was a dragon.

171
00:11:11.060 --> 00:11:13.030
He laid waste to our people.

172
00:11:15.520 --> 00:11:17.070
You remember Cerkonos?

173
00:11:17.270 --> 00:11:20.120
Of course.
Winds watch you. Headmaster.

174
00:11:20.320 --> 00:11:22.160
And you. Keyleth.

175
00:11:22.360 --> 00:11:24.330
I came as soon as I could.

176
00:11:24.530 --> 00:11:26.750
But our brothers and sisters
were already decimated.

177
00:11:28.950 --> 00:11:32.250
If we can't find
a way to close the rift soon.

178
00:11:32.450 --> 00:11:34.800
the Fire Dominion
will consume ours

179
00:11:35.000 --> 00:11:37.070
and remain open forever.

180
00:11:38.240 --> 00:11:41.110
Keyleth. I need you
to come with me.

181
00:11:42.320 --> 00:11:44.850
Normally. the lodestones
keep the gateway sealed.

182
00:11:45.050 --> 00:11:46.980
But when the dragon
destroyed them.

183
00:11:47.180 --> 00:11:48.650
the rift was torn open.

184
00:11:48.850 --> 00:11:51.070
Those beasts have been
coming through in waves

185
00:11:51.260 --> 00:11:53.570
while our firetamers
hold them back.

186
00:11:53.770 --> 00:11:55.690
How do we close the rift?

187
00:11:55.890 --> 00:11:57.910
By controlling
the flames themselves.

188
00:11:58.100 --> 00:11:59.880
The two of us.

189
00:12:01.050 --> 00:12:02.830
Dad. I-I don't know if I...

190
00:12:03.030 --> 00:12:05.950
We're lucky you came.
You've been on your Aramenté.

191
00:12:06.150 --> 00:12:09.750
Your mastery of fire
must be far beyond ours.

192
00:12:09.950 --> 00:12:11.380
Uh. you would think.

193
00:12:11.580 --> 00:12:14.600
The firetamers need
our magic to seal it.

194
00:12:17.520 --> 00:12:19.510
More of these fuckers?

195
00:12:19.710 --> 00:12:21.430
- I've brought help!
- Huh?

196
00:12:21.630 --> 00:12:23.810
No freaking way. Keyleth?

197
00:12:24.010 --> 00:12:26.700
Kima? Allura.

198
00:12:28.790 --> 00:12:30.100
But you guys are dead.

199
00:12:30.300 --> 00:12:32.190
We're very much alive.

200
00:12:32.390 --> 00:12:34.120
Where's the rest of your team?

201
00:12:37.250 --> 00:12:40.610
Oh. God.
It was a massacre.

202
00:12:40.810 --> 00:12:42.880
Anyone have eyes on Keyleth?

203
00:12:45.430 --> 00:12:47.160
Oh. yeah.

204
00:12:47.360 --> 00:12:49.670
You know what
you fight fire with?

205
00:12:49.860 --> 00:12:51.500
- Fire?
- Me.

206
00:12:54.160 --> 00:12:55.670
Trinket. time to get to work.

207
00:12:58.940 --> 00:13:01.430
Scanlan. word. please.

208
00:13:01.630 --> 00:13:03.436
Just say yes to that favor.
and it's all yours.

209
00:13:03.460 --> 00:13:06.140
I hope you fall
into lava. asshat!

210
00:13:06.340 --> 00:13:08.600
Well. that wasn't a no.

211
00:13:08.800 --> 00:13:10.850
♪ <i>Let's crank up the heat</i> ♪

212
00:13:13.390 --> 00:13:15.980
- Scanlan.
- Keyleth. if we fetch your friends.

213
00:13:16.180 --> 00:13:18.070
can you buy us some time?

214
00:13:18.270 --> 00:13:21.070
I mean. we can certainly try.

215
00:13:21.270 --> 00:13:22.700
Huh?

216
00:13:22.900 --> 00:13:24.470
One's coming through!

217
00:13:26.860 --> 00:13:28.640
- It's going.
- Hold.

218
00:13:33.160 --> 00:13:35.590
I hunger.

219
00:13:35.790 --> 00:13:37.170
Feed me.

220
00:13:37.370 --> 00:13:41.930
Well. I'm trying. but none of
these guys got bloody insides.

221
00:13:42.130 --> 00:13:43.550
- What was that. buddy?
- Uh...

222
00:13:43.750 --> 00:13:46.850
I just love me
some blueberry pie.

223
00:13:47.050 --> 00:13:49.740
- Wh-What?
- Shit. shit. I am very flammable!

224
00:14:04.380 --> 00:14:05.450
Hey.

225
00:14:05.650 --> 00:14:07.240
Wait. what?

226
00:14:07.440 --> 00:14:09.790
Allura fucking Vysoren.

227
00:14:09.990 --> 00:14:12.710
Not my middle name. but
I'm pleased to see you as well.

228
00:14:12.910 --> 00:14:15.640
Quickly. Keyleth and her father
need our help.

229
00:14:17.520 --> 00:14:20.090
How are you here?
In Emon. we saw...

230
00:14:20.290 --> 00:14:21.940
Allura saved us.

231
00:14:23.650 --> 00:14:25.180
<i>When the tower fell.</i>

232
00:14:25.380 --> 00:14:28.100
<i>she whisked us away
at the last second.</i>

233
00:14:28.300 --> 00:14:29.390
<i>Nearly shat my armor.</i>

234
00:14:29.590 --> 00:14:31.390
We knew if Thordak was free.

235
00:14:31.590 --> 00:14:33.140
it meant the rift was open.

236
00:14:33.340 --> 00:14:35.440
Hold up. Thordak
came through Pyrah?

237
00:14:35.640 --> 00:14:37.690
How did you even know
it was him?

238
00:14:37.890 --> 00:14:40.980
Because we are the reason
he escaped.

239
00:14:41.180 --> 00:14:44.070
<i>Years ago. Kima and I
battled Thordak</i>

240
00:14:44.270 --> 00:14:46.260
<i>with a group not unlike yours.</i>

241
00:14:50.900 --> 00:14:53.660
<i>But we were outmatched.</i>

242
00:14:53.860 --> 00:14:55.670
<i>In a desperate attempt.</i>

243
00:14:55.870 --> 00:14:58.130
<i>we got hold
of an ancient artifact.</i>

244
00:14:58.330 --> 00:15:00.420
<i>the Soul Anchor.</i>

245
00:15:00.620 --> 00:15:03.260
<i>and decided to bind him to it.</i>

246
00:15:03.460 --> 00:15:07.240
<i>Like an arcane tether. it pulled
Thordak into the Fire Plane...</i>

247
00:15:09.570 --> 00:15:11.780
<i>imprisoning him
there forever.</i>

248
00:15:12.820 --> 00:15:14.350
Or so we thought.

249
00:15:18.410 --> 00:15:21.630
Come. Stay close.

250
00:15:23.670 --> 00:15:25.530
All right. Keyleth. this is it.

251
00:15:25.730 --> 00:15:27.450
No. I-I can't. I can't do it.

252
00:15:27.650 --> 00:15:30.870
Of course you can.
You're as strong as your mother.

253
00:15:31.070 --> 00:15:33.430
Maybe even stronger.

254
00:15:44.060 --> 00:15:45.230
Now!

255
00:16:01.920 --> 00:16:03.280
Yes.

256
00:16:03.470 --> 00:16:04.790
Good work. Keyleth.

257
00:16:07.460 --> 00:16:08.490
Oh. no.

258
00:16:15.640 --> 00:16:17.560
Careful.

259
00:16:19.350 --> 00:16:20.350
Look out!

260
00:16:24.150 --> 00:16:25.960
Damn it. it's widening.

261
00:16:35.990 --> 00:16:37.600
I hunger.

262
00:16:37.800 --> 00:16:40.400
What? They don't got no blood.

263
00:16:40.600 --> 00:16:43.860
Then find me
some... now.

264
00:16:44.060 --> 00:16:45.830
Huh?

265
00:16:47.500 --> 00:16:49.400
I need higher ground.

266
00:16:49.600 --> 00:16:51.660
Okay. fine. It's "Volantire."

267
00:16:51.860 --> 00:16:54.470
Volantire?

268
00:16:57.140 --> 00:16:58.430
That's more like it.

269
00:17:06.310 --> 00:17:07.760
We're losing control.

270
00:17:07.960 --> 00:17:10.020
Everybody. gather round!

271
00:17:12.780 --> 00:17:13.890
Together.

272
00:17:25.680 --> 00:17:27.130
Dad!

273
00:17:28.130 --> 00:17:29.650
Pike!

274
00:17:29.850 --> 00:17:32.170
Oh. no. I got him.

275
00:17:34.340 --> 00:17:36.200
I'm sorry. Dad.

276
00:17:36.400 --> 00:17:39.620
The truth is.
I haven't finished my trials.

277
00:17:39.820 --> 00:17:43.290
I... I'm too scared.
I'm not ready.

278
00:17:51.070 --> 00:17:53.900
<i>Little Flower. listen.</i>

279
00:18:00.580 --> 00:18:02.580
<i>Listen.</i>

280
00:18:07.330 --> 00:18:09.860
Behind you! Vex!

281
00:18:13.020 --> 00:18:15.870
<i>Listen to your power.</i>

282
00:18:16.070 --> 00:18:19.330
- Damn it!
- There's too many of them!

283
00:18:25.600 --> 00:18:29.340
I am Keyleth. an Air Ashari.

284
00:18:29.540 --> 00:18:31.970
like my mother before me.

285
00:18:37.990 --> 00:18:39.610
Keyleth. what are you doing?

286
00:18:43.660 --> 00:18:44.870
Keyleth?

287
00:18:50.420 --> 00:18:53.340
I was made to pass through fire.

288
00:18:54.340 --> 00:18:55.960
Keyleth!

289
00:19:12.440 --> 00:19:14.190
The Fire Plane.

290
00:19:17.650 --> 00:19:19.200
Aah! It hurts!

291
00:19:20.820 --> 00:19:22.740
Only if I let it.

292
00:19:31.120 --> 00:19:33.330
I can hear it.

293
00:20:22.220 --> 00:20:24.330
Keyleth!

294
00:20:24.530 --> 00:20:26.720
No.

295
00:20:48.340 --> 00:20:50.350
My child.

296
00:20:50.550 --> 00:20:52.790
- I thought...
- I'm okay. Dad.

297
00:20:54.080 --> 00:20:55.080
- What?
- Keyleth.

298
00:20:55.220 --> 00:20:56.220
Keyleth. you're all right.

299
00:20:56.310 --> 00:20:57.320
Oh. my God.

300
00:20:59.270 --> 00:21:00.910
Holy shit. that was close.

301
00:21:01.110 --> 00:21:02.880
Gave me a heart attack.

302
00:21:04.680 --> 00:21:07.180
Think you'll be needing this.

303
00:21:16.270 --> 00:21:19.090
Keyleth of the Air Ashari.

304
00:21:19.290 --> 00:21:23.600
from this day forward.
you have the blessing of Pyrah.

305
00:21:23.790 --> 00:21:26.930
Your water and earth trials
await you on your Aramenté.

306
00:21:27.130 --> 00:21:31.100
But go forth. knowing
you have mastered fire.

307
00:21:31.300 --> 00:21:33.400
Thank you. Flamespeaker.

308
00:21:33.600 --> 00:21:36.820
And a word of warning
on your journeys.

309
00:21:37.020 --> 00:21:38.610
Thordak escaped with aid

310
00:21:38.810 --> 00:21:41.780
from someone posing
as one of our own.

311
00:21:41.980 --> 00:21:44.870
Be sure you trust
those around you.

312
00:21:45.070 --> 00:21:47.910
and truly know their hearts.

313
00:21:48.110 --> 00:21:50.300
I'd trust them with my life.

314
00:21:52.600 --> 00:21:55.040
Quite the look.

315
00:21:55.240 --> 00:21:57.000
Mind telling us
how you did that?

316
00:21:57.200 --> 00:21:58.550
When the fire took me.

317
00:21:58.750 --> 00:22:01.800
I could feel the connection
between the planes.

318
00:22:02.000 --> 00:22:03.720
Traveling between planes.

319
00:22:03.920 --> 00:22:05.430
Hmm. could be handy.

320
00:22:05.630 --> 00:22:06.850
Think you could do it again?

321
00:22:07.050 --> 00:22:09.310
Only one way to find out.

322
00:22:09.510 --> 00:22:14.080
I couldn't have asked for better
companions for my dear Keyleth.

323
00:22:15.120 --> 00:22:16.690
Until we meet again.

324
00:22:16.890 --> 00:22:18.780
please take care of each other.

325
00:22:18.970 --> 00:22:21.840
Hmm. Especially that one.

326
00:22:24.590 --> 00:22:26.200
Hey. you guys coming with?

327
00:22:26.400 --> 00:22:29.120
Charging into the fray
like the good old days?

328
00:22:29.320 --> 00:22:30.870
Afraid not.

329
00:22:31.070 --> 00:22:33.250
We'll do what we can
to help rebuild Pyrah.

330
00:22:33.450 --> 00:22:37.140
then head to Whitestone
so this one can heal.

331
00:22:39.150 --> 00:22:41.630
Plus. we got to check on
what happened to Syngorn.

332
00:22:41.830 --> 00:22:44.090
Whole city just bugged out
when the dragons showed up.

333
00:22:44.290 --> 00:22:45.300
Elves.

334
00:22:45.500 --> 00:22:47.200
Skittish bunch of bastards.

335
00:22:50.200 --> 00:22:52.060
Oi. Scanlan.

336
00:22:52.260 --> 00:22:54.230
- Mm. Hmm?
- Thanks for earlier.

337
00:22:54.430 --> 00:22:56.150
That was actually kind of you.

338
00:22:56.350 --> 00:22:59.360
I mean. what was I gonna do.
let you die? Again?

339
00:22:59.560 --> 00:23:03.650
And because I'm so mature now.
I accept your terms.

340
00:23:03.850 --> 00:23:06.110
I hereby owe you one favor.

341
00:23:06.310 --> 00:23:09.700
Anything. to be cashed in
at a time of your choosing.

342
00:23:09.900 --> 00:23:13.120
Ooh.
This is gonna be fun.

343
00:23:13.320 --> 00:23:15.540
Trinket. care to seal the deal?

344
00:23:17.910 --> 00:23:19.290
Hmm?

345
00:23:19.490 --> 00:23:21.210
Oh. come on. Oh.

346
00:23:21.410 --> 00:23:23.970
Hate that bear.

347
00:23:31.740 --> 00:23:34.730
Get back here.

348
00:23:36.970 --> 00:23:38.400
Huh?

349
00:23:38.600 --> 00:23:41.710
Insects.

350
00:23:49.340 --> 00:23:51.450
Yes.

351
00:23:51.650 --> 00:23:55.040
This gold pleases us.

352
00:23:55.240 --> 00:23:56.620
For now.

353
00:23:56.820 --> 00:23:59.750
And the herd
will keep paying tribute.

354
00:23:59.950 --> 00:24:01.460
For now.

355
00:24:01.660 --> 00:24:03.590
For always.

356
00:24:03.790 --> 00:24:07.130
Nations will quake and tremble

357
00:24:07.330 --> 00:24:10.720
under the reign
of the Chroma Conclave.

358
00:24:10.920 --> 00:24:14.930
A reign that will
sadly be short-lived.

359
00:24:15.130 --> 00:24:20.230
Unless. that is. you care
to hear what I have to say.

360
00:24:20.430 --> 00:24:22.370
Hmm...

361
00:24:28.350 --> 00:24:30.910
♪ <i>In an outhouse</i>
<i>on the edge of the world</i> ♪

362
00:24:31.110 --> 00:24:35.430
♪ <i>Our hearts beat as one</i> ♪

363
00:24:36.850 --> 00:24:39.790
♪ <i>It's where it all</i> ♪

364
00:24:39.990 --> 00:24:44.000
♪ <i>Begun</i> ♪

365
00:24:44.200 --> 00:24:50.090
♪ <i>Standing there</i>
<i>in that privy line</i> ♪

366
00:24:50.290 --> 00:24:54.990
♪ <i>Couldn't help but blush</i> ♪

367
00:24:56.490 --> 00:25:01.980
♪ <i>You sitting in the dark</i> ♪

368
00:25:02.180 --> 00:25:07.240
♪ <i>Me waiting for that flush</i> ♪

369
00:25:07.430 --> 00:25:09.090
♪ <i>Of love</i> ♪

370
00:25:12.720 --> 00:25:14.680
Chirp.

